DESCRIPTION:Building: Jackson Gym\nCity: Somerville\, MA 02144\nRoom: Da
 nce Lab\nCampus: Medford/Somerville campus\nLocation Details: Jackson Da
 nce Lab\, 50 Talbot Avenue\, Medford\, MA 02155\nWheelchair Accessible: 
 Yes\nOpen to Public: Yes\nPrimary Audience: Alumni and Friends\,Faculty
 \,Interns and Residents\,Parents\,Postdoctoral Fellows\,Staff\,Students (
 Graduate)\,Students (Postdoctoral)\,Students (Undergraduate)\nEvent Type
 : Performance\nEvent Subject: Theater/Dance\nEvent Sponsor: School of Ar
 ts and Sciences\nEvent Sponsor Department / Area: Theatre\, Dance\, and 
 Performance Studies department\nEvent Sponsor Details: Tufts Dance Progr
 am\nAdmission/Cost: Free and Open to the Public\nEvent Contact Name: Jen
 ny Oliver\nEvent Contact Email: Jenny.Oliver@tufts.edu\nEvent Contact Ph
 one: 617-627-2556\n\nConscious Movement: Swift Charakterz\, BreakSesh\, 
 and the Question of Commodification\n\nAn interactive demonstration of B
 reakin’ as community dance practice. Over the course of 45 minutes to an
  hour\, Swift Charakterz invites you to get involved. The demonstration 
 blends workshop elements with an ongoing cypher\, allowing participants 
 to get involved to whatever degree they are interested in (e.g. observin
 g the cypher\, learning on the side one-on-one with members of the crew
 \, dancing the circle). There will be a DJ cutting the music live.\n\nFre
 e and open to the public. No registration required. Free parking availab
 le.
CATEGORIES:Theatre, Dance, and Performance Studies
